<p>We didn’t have this problem in the past. It used to just fire once which makes me think its a problem with the PCM. I’m probably wrong though.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    public void execute() {
        boolean climb = stickToggle.getAsBoolean();
        if (climb) {
            climber.toggleClimber();
        }
    }</code></pre>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2021-10-05T21:16:50.019Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":110,"readers_count":109,"score":32.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":396398,"topic_slug":"pneumatic-rapid-firing-problem","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":4999,"username":"Nate_Laverdure","name":"Nate Laverdure (he/him)","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nate_laverdure/{size}/134005_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":49423,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)"},"post_url":"/t/pneumatic-rapid-firing-problem/396398/3","custom_user_title":"2815A (19-23) | 190M (23...)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2970717,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-05T21:28:03.674Z","cooked":"<p>I’m not sure what class stickToggle is, but depending on how it’s implemented, my guess is that <code>getAsBoolean()</code> returns true if the button is active and false if it’s not active.  So the loop will run multiple times with climb = true, which will call toggleClimber() multiple times.  What you probably want is <code>stickToggle.getPressed()</code> or equivalent (on the WPILib Joystick class, the Pressed() functions do a rising edge detect and will return true only once until the button is released and pressed again).  If the classes you’re using don’t have “pressed” style functionality, you can achieve the same goal with an instance variable to save the previous state:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">boolean prevClimb;

public void execute() {
    boolean climb = stickToggle.getAsBoolean();
    if (climb &amp;&amp; !prevClimb) {
        climber.toggleClimber();
    }
    prevClimb = climb;
}
</code></pre>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2021-10-06T00:16:37.303Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":95,"readers_count":94,"score":34.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":396398,"topic_slug":"pneumatic-rapid-firing-problem","display_username":"Peter Johnson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":49423,"username":"Gandagorn","name":"Elliot Scher","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13575,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA"},"post_url":"/t/pneumatic-rapid-firing-problem/396398/4","custom_user_title":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":2970752,"name":"Elliot Scher","username":"Gandagorn","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gandagorn/{size}/267112_2.png","created_at":"2021-10-06T00:16:55.237Z","cooked":"<p>Just implemented. Thanks so much!!!</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2021-10-06T00:16:55.237Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":65,"readers_count":64,"score":18.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":396398,"topic_slug":"pneumatic-rapid-firing-problem","display_username":"Elliot Scher","primary_group_name":null,"flair